1 F. Every applicant for the certificate of certified public
2 accountant shall provide evidence of successful completion of an
3 ethics examination prescribed by the Board.
4 G. Every applicant for the certificate of certified public
5 accountant shall submit to a national criminal history record check
6 in accordance with Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma
7 Statutes. Results of national criminal history record checks shall
8 be provided to the Oklahoma Accountancy Board by the Oklahoma State
9 Bureau of Investigation. Criminal history record check results are
10 confidential and shall not be disseminated outside the Oklahoma
11 Accountancy Board. The costs associated with the national criminal
12 history record check shall be paid by the applicant.
13 H. An individual applying for a certificate as a certified
14 public accountant must make application for the certificate within
15 five (5) years of the date the Board notifies the candidate that the
16 candidate has successfully passed all sections of the C.P.A.
17 Examination. If the candidate fails to make application for the
18 certificate within five (5) years, the candidate must provide
19 documentation showing he or she has completed at least one hundred
20 twenty (120) hours of qualifying continuing public accountancy
21 education completed within the three-year period immediately
22 preceding the date the individual applies for certification. The
23 Board shall establish rules whereby time limits set for application
24 pursuant to this provision may, upon written application to the
Req. No. 12143 Page 6
1 Boar d, be waived or reduced if the candidate is called to active
2 military service or becomes incapacitated as a result of illness or
3 injury or for such other good causes as determined by the Board on a
4 case-by-case basis.
5 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
